Always use /docs/metrics_specification.md as the source of truth for all metric calculations.  Always use /docs/portfolio_construction_policy.md as the source of truth for portfolio construction (single-stage max-return optimizer, per-asset RC caps, liquidity, mandate), feasibility checks, and optimization constraints.  For stress testing (scenarios, Loss/RC concentration tests, factor and historical validation, outputs), use docs/docs/stress_testing_spec.md as the source of truth.  Also use /docs/data_policy_nan_young_etfs.md for data policy, NaN handling, young ETFs, dynamic NaN-safe backtest (global equal redistribution among risk tickers, RC-gated fallback to cash), and baseline vs full reporting.  Do not invent alternative portfolio construction rules if the policy file already defines them.  If a task conflicts with the policy, explicitly flag the conflict instead of silently overriding the rules.  Before coding, first restate which rules from the specification and portfolio policy apply to the current task.
